@0    = ~We're tracking a half-orc, Dorn Il-Khan. He passed this way. Have you seen him?~
@1    = ~I'm tracking a half-orc, Dorn Il-Khan. He passed this way. Have you seen him?~
@2    = ~There is a summoning circle within the gorge. I would seek it out.~
@3    = ~He entered the gorge ahead of ye. The land recoiled at his passing, but I lacked the strength to stop him.~
@4    = ~Yer senses have not misled ye. This blight runs deeper than root or stone.~
@5    = ~Three summoning stones were bound in Vernus' ritual, and they remain within the gorge.~
@6    = ~Should they fall into the wrong hands, I fear the portal's gate may be opened once more.~
@7    = ~If Dorn remains within the gorge, he will bring further harm. I cannot turn back now.~
@8    = ~So be it. Listen carefully.~
@9    = ~The beast trapped within threatens all. It must be dealt with.~
@10   = ~If Dorn Il-Khan fled into the gorge, then I must follow and bring him to justice.~
